      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Control Structures\n",
        "\n",
        "An (imperative) programming language is not really usable without control structures. Python also provides several:\n",
        "- conditional branching: when we do not necessarily want to execute a sequence of statements (`if`)\n",
        "- repetition while a condition holds (`while`)\n",
        "- element-wise repetition: when we want to perform the same operations on every element of a known-length structure (`for`)\n",
        "\n",
        "In Python the control structure always refers to the code section that is indented after it.\n",
        "(So it absolutely matters whether we indent something or not!)"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4bDkdD1wPMIk"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Conditional Branching\n",
        "\n",
        "After the `if` keyword there must be an expression that has a truth value, followed by a colon. The conditional execution applies to the lines indented after the condition.\n",
        "\n",
        "After `if ...:` there may be an `else:`.\n",
        "This branch executes when the condition is *not* true.\n",
        "If we want additional branches, we can use the `elif` keyword."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "Ik56TLquQCjS"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# the input function allows us to ask the user for data\n",
        "number = int(input(\"Please enter an integer: \"))\n",
        "\n",
        "# simple conditional execution:\n",
        "if number == 0:\n",
        "    # this part is indented, so the condition applies to it\n",
        "    print(\"The entered number is zero.\")\n",
        "    print(\"This line also prints when the number is zero.\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# multiple-branch conditional execution:\n",
        "if number % 2 == 0:\n",
        "    print(\"The entered number is even.\")\n",
        "elif number % 3 == 0:\n",
        "    print(\"The entered number is divisible by three.\")\n",
        "elif number % 5 == 0:\n",
        "    print(\"The entered number is divisible by five.\")\n",
        "else:\n",
        "    print(\"The entered number is too complicated, choose another.\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "2ZCgX6B4QX72"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Conditional Repetition (`while`)\n",
        "\n",
        "After the `while` keyword, there is also an expression with a truth value.\n",
        "As long as it is considered true, the loop body (the indented part) repeats."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "kLdbDN6kTZU1"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "entered_text = ''\n",
        "\n",
        "# as long as `entered_text` is not numeric, we keep asking again and again\n",
        "while not entered_text.isnumeric():\n",
        "    entered_text = input(\"Please enter an integer: \")\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"The entered number: {entered_text}\")"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "yq8MMoojT09L"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# Generate a sequence starting from 1, where the next element is obtained\n",
        "# by multiplying the previous number by 5, appending the first digit of\n",
        "# the resulting value to the end, and then if it is even dividing by 2.\n",
        "# Stop if the result becomes greater than one million.\n",
        "\n",
        "current_number = 1\n",
        "while current_number <= 1_000_000:\n",
        "    multiplied = current_number * 5\n",
        "    appended_str = str(multiplied) + str(multiplied)[0]\n",
        "    current_number = int(appended_str)\n",
        "    if current_number % 2 == 0:\n",
        "        current_number = current_number // 2\n",
        "    print(current_number)\n"
      ],
