      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Element-wise Repetition (`for`)\n",
        "\n",
        "The purpose of the `for` loop is to execute statements for every element of a known-length structure.\n",
        "We do this either just to repeat the statements as many times as there are elements, or usually because we want to do something with each element."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "L-xT_CM8aRQu"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "my_list = [1, 2, 3, 88, 0]\n",
        "for element in my_list:\n",
        "    print(\"the next element:\", element)"
      ],
